attachments.fallback: FiveThirtyEight: Texas A&M Pulled Off A 1-in-3,000 Comeback

text: late, but i kept watching that a&m comeback last night on youtube cause i didn’t see it live, so crazy
I accidentally saw it live. Was watching the score at dinner then tuned in on the drive home to watch those 30 seconds. Absolutely nuts.
I had a similar experience with that UNI buzzer beater in rd 1. Was at a bar in Lincoln City getting a drink, looked up at the TV for the last possession and was like “holy shit!"
I get the whole CBS/TNT/TrueTV/TBS thing, but I really liked it when it was all on CBS and they hit you with the last five mins of every game, rapid fire.
it was like Redzone Channel before Redzone Channel
The new Apple TV app lets you do two games side by side, but it would be nice if it had smart switching (and wasn’t full of bugs)
